review_text: My four-legged child tends to get anxious and pants non-stop after daily walks or zoomie sessions, especially when she knows she’s knocked something over that she shouldn’t have. She can pant for up to 45 minutes or even an hour, and sometimes at night, she’s too wound up from playtime to sleep, throwing little tantrums instead. Healthy Calm has been a lifesaver! Giving her just one chew, while staying by her side and petting her, calms her down, and she’ll eventually lay beside me and fall asleep, staying restful through the night. I only give it to her when really needed, but it’s incredibly effective when we’re out of ideas on how to soothe her. Highly recommend it for anyone dealing with a similarly anxious pup!

My 15 yr old poodle has become very timid due to his failing eyesight and is shaking badly whenever it rains (and it rains alot in Malaysia), He also paces up and down the room in the middle of the night. This pill seems to help and after taking it he stopped pacing and shaking and also sleeps throughout the night.

Healthy Pup, Healthy Calm is a great solution for those who want to help their pet cope with anxiety. I noticed that after starting to use these chewable tablets, my dog became much calmer during loud noises and changes in the environment. They have a pleasant taste, and my pet eats them with pleasure, which makes the process of taking them easy and pleasant. The composition is rich in natural ingredients, which gives confidence in the safety of the product. I recommend it to all dog owners who have problems with anxiety in their pets!

I decided to buy this anti-anxiety remedy for my dog, because he often gets nervous and his nervous system is too excitable. At first, I was a little alarmed by the fact that the composition includes melatonin and I would not like to give the dog hormones. But we still decided to try it and the quality of these chewing gum pleased us. I don't give them often, only when there is a great need, and they are really effective, they relieve stress and anxiety attacks in my boy. He likes the taste of these pills and eats them with joy. I will not advise you to buy this product, because here everyone decides for himself and weighs all the risks. It is better to consult a veterinarian.
